  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Human Resource / Administrative Officer",
  "description": "<p>Roles & Responsibilities</p><p>The HR / Admin Executive is responsible for <strong>full HR administration, regulatory compliance, and operational support</strong> in a licensed security company.</p><p><strong>Core Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Handle <strong>end-to-end Human Resource and administrative functions</strong> for security operations</p></li><li><p><strong>Answer and manage all incoming office calls</strong>, including staff, clients, sites, and regulatory bodies</p></li><li><p>Act as first point of contact for security officers regarding attendance, deployment, leave, and HR matters</p></li><li><p>Manage recruitment, onboarding, deployment, and exit processes for security personnel</p></li><li><p>Prepare employment contracts, confirmation letters, disciplinary letters, and HR documentation</p></li><li><p>Maintain accurate employee records, licensing status, and personnel files</p></li></ul><p><strong>Security Industry & Compliance Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Ensure compliance with <strong>PRD and MOM </strong>requirements</p></li><li><p>Track and monitor security officer licences, training validity, and renewal deadlines</p></li><li><p>Support PRD inspections, audits, and document submissions</p></li><li><p>Liaise with PRD, MOM, training providers, and relevant authorities when required</p></li><li><p>Assist with Work Permit applications, renewals, cancellations, and MOM reporting</p></li></ul><p><strong>Operational & Payroll Support:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Coordinate with Operations team on manpower deployment and scheduling</p></li><li><p>Collect and verify attendance, overtime, and relief deployment records</p></li><li><p>Prepare payroll inputs and ensure accurate submission to payroll processor</p></li><li><p>Handle leave tracking, medical certificates, and absenteeism reporting</p></li></ul><p><strong>Administrative Duties:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Maintain office records, filing systems, and HR trackers</p></li><li><p>Draft emails, internal memos, and official correspondence</p></li><li><p>Support management with HR reports and compliance documentation</p></li></ul><h3>Requirements:</h3><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in Human Resource Management, Business Administration, or related field</p></li><li><p><strong>Experience in security, manpower, or operations-based industries is strongly preferred</strong></p></li><li><p>Familiar with <strong>PRD and MOM regulations</strong> or willing to learn quickly</p></li><li><p>Able to handle high call volume and operational issues professionally</p></li><li><p>Organized, firm, and able to manage confidential information</p></li><li><p>Comfortable working in a fast-paced, compliance-driven environment</p></li></ul>",
